Project 4B

Include files:
> lab4b.c: the source file

> Makefile: for build, run check program, generate tarball and clear files

> README: the introduction of the files

To run this program, you must copy the files to the beaglebone board or any other embedded system with Linux system and MRAA library:

make default: build the executable file
make check: run the specific shell script to test some common cases like START, STOP, OFF, etc.
make dist: generate tarball 
make clean: clear the generated files

Resources:
1. http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/fcntl.2.html
2. http://wiki.seeedstudio.com/Grove-Temperature_Sensor_V1.2/
3. http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/poll.2.html
4. https://iotdk.intel.com/docs/master/mraa/index.html